<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="187" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4763: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-17">November 17,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>7283. With reference to your 7867 November 11, Department concurs in
                        procedure for approval of minutes of Executive Committee as outlined in
                        despatch 12063, November 4.<note n="90" xml:id="d187fn90">Not
                            printed.</note>
                    </p>
                    <p>Concerning relations between IGC and UNRRA Department will delay instructions
                        in view of discussions taking place at Atlantic City Conference.</p>
                    <p>We believe it inadvisable for IGC representative to attend Atlantic City
                        Conference at this time. Matter has been discussed with Mr. Myron Taylor who
                        concurs in this view.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>